         <abstract id="aspace_a773bc8e03b665b415d7e806c7472eee">This collection documents the work of Southern Presbyterian missionaries Waddy Hampton Hudson, his wife Maude Chapin Hudson, and their son George A. Hudson, primarily in Kashing, China (now Jiaxing, Zhejiang Province) from 1894 to 1940. Waddy Hudson was in charge of mission accounts, trained ministers, and preached in neighboring villages, traveling from Kashing in a house boat. George Hudson worked initially in Kashing and then in Taiwan following World War II, including a tent evangelism ministry.</abstract>
